<HEADLINE>
FT  07 SEP 93 / London Stock Exchange: Insurers switch
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER JOHN, CHRISTOPHER PRICE, JOEL KIBAZO and TOM FORD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A pre-results recommendation sent insurer Legal &amp; General higher yesterday
at the expense of Prudential. Securities house UBS repeated its
recommendation to switch out of the Pru, which publishes interim figures
tomorrow, and into L&amp;G, which announces its profits next Thursday.
UBS is cautious on the life sector after the recent announcement by the
Office of Fair Trading on disclosure of commissions. However, it feels that
L&amp;G offers the best value and forecasts interim profits of Pounds 78m,
against Pounds 74m last time. It predicts profits of Pounds 250m for
Prudential against Pounds 249m previously. L&amp;G gained 8 at 476p while
Prudential put on a penny at 337p.
</TEXT>
