<HEADLINE>
FT  07 SEP 93 / International Company News: Mediobanca plans issue
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MILAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MEDIOBANCA, the Italian merchant bank which was a big shareholder in the
collapsed Ferruzzi Finanziaria group, yesterday announced lower profits and
plans for a rights issue, Reuter reports from Milan.
Net profits for the year ended June were L200.1bn (Dollars 126m), compared
with 262.1bn a year earlier.
Bad debt provision was L275.2bn, up from L153.1bn. The dividend is being
increased by 10 per cent to L200 a share.
The bank is proposing a scrip and rights issue to increase nominal share
capital to L476bn from L340bn.
There is to be a one-for-10 scrip issue and a three-for-10 rights offer at
L10,000 a share. A total of 102m new shares will be issued in this way.
</TEXT>
