<HEADLINE>
FT  07 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Acquisitions help Wills advance to Pounds
1.56m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN MURRELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
WILLS GROUP, the expanding distributor of high specification fluid handling
equipment, achieved a profits rise from Pounds 519,000 to Pounds 1.56m
pre-tax for the year ended July 3.
The figures included a two months' contribution from Platon International,
the former USM-quoted instrumentation company acquired for Pounds 2.7m.
Along with the purchase, which followed the acquisition of Lightfoot
Refrigeration in December, a 1-for-3 rights issue was launched to raise
Pounds 5.2m.
The money raised will help restructure Platon's finances and develop new
products.
Group turnover for the year expanded from Pounds 15m to Pounds 19.28m,
including Pounds 1.33m from acquisitions. Interest charges were cut to
Pounds 45,000 (Pounds 133,000).
Earnings per share improved from 0.72p to 1.6p basic, or from 0.6p to 1.28p
diluted. A final dividend of 0.3p makes a 0.4p (0.1p) total.
The directors hoped the first six months would see further progress in
profitability as sales and profits are weighted towards the second half.
