FT  07 SEP 93 / Labour attacks premium rises
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A LABOUR party survey shows that the average family faces a 19 per cent
increase in its household insurance bill this year, Richard Lapper writes.
The survey of premiums set by nine companies in 11 areas also shows that the
highest quote is likely to be 2 1/2 -times more expensive than the cheapest.
Mr Robin Cook, shadow trade and industry secretary, said: 'Customers are
getting a raw deal. I want to see these insurance companies make clear to
their policyholders by how much premiums are being increased, and then to
justify their behaviour. They should not get away with exploiting consumers
in this way.'
