<HEADLINE>
FT  07 SEP 93 / Jail riot report due in weeks
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A REPORT on the riot at Wymott Prison in Lancashire is likely to be with
Home Secretary Michael Howard before the end of the month, it emerged
yesterday. The Home Office said initial estimates of the damage were between
Pounds 10m and Pounds 20m.
Judge Stephen Tumim, the chief inspector of prisons, will lead the inquiry.
He will report directly to the Home Secretary, who will decide whether to
publish all or parts of his findings.
The riot echoed an outbreak of violence in April 1986, when 200 prisoners
went on the rampage causing 'immense' damage.
Prison sources said yesterday it was hoped that an interim report, either
oral or written, would be given to Mr Howard before the end of the month
with the full written report to follow soon after.
