FT  06 SEP 93 / Consumer confidence improved in August says survey
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NEIL BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CONSUMER confidence improved last month but it is still too early to predict
a steady recovery in spending, says a survey carried out by NOP for Verdict,
the retail market research group, Neil Buckley writes.
The index for August was 118, up from 112 in June and July - and well above
the 109 in August last year - but still below the 125 reached in May.
