<HEADLINE>
FT  06 SEP 93 / Part-timers prove shy of unions
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TRADE UNIONS are finding it increasingly hard to recruit part-time workers,
a survey published yesterday by Labour Research magazine shows.
It found only 16 per cent of the combined membership of the country's 20
largest unions are part-timers although as many as 28 per cent of the
workforce now work part-time, of which four out of five are women. Labour
Research calculates only 22 per cent of part-timers are in unions, compared
with a quarter of them five years ago.
